dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.address.IPAddress
dataStructure.description:
This class represents an IP address. It can be either in v4 or v6 form, and can be formatted as dotted decimal or CIDR. One or more host aliases can also be supplied.

This entity is abstract

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: IPAddress

child.name: networkNumber
child.description:
This contains the network number portion of the IP Address.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: networkNumber

child.name: hostNumber
child.description:
This contains the host number portion of the IP Address.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: hostNumber

child.name: subnetMask
child.description:
This is a string attribute that defines the subnet mask for the IP Address of this instance. The IP Address is constructed by concatenating the networkNumber and the hostNumber, forming a dotted decimal IP Address. The subnetMask is formatted according to the appropriate convention as defined in the addressFormat attribute of this object.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: subnetMask
